        <num>CCP 645</num>
        <heading>645.  Pleading nonjoinder of a party</heading>
        <content>
          <p>Art. 645.  Pleading nonjoinder of a party
The failure to join a party to an action may be pleaded in the peremptory exception, or may be noticed by the trial or appellate court on its own motion.</p>
        </content>
